org.pac4j.play

Class CallbackController

  • java.lang.Object
    • play.mvc.Results
      • play.mvc.Controller
        • org.pac4j.play.CallbackController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    play.mvc.Http.HeaderNames, play.mvc.Http.Status
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JavaController

    public class CallbackController
extends play.mvc.Controller
    This controller is the class to finish the authentication process and logout the user.

    Public methods : callback(), logoutAndOk() and logoutAndRedirect() must be used in the routes file.

    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Jerome Leleu

    • Method Detail

      • callback

        public static play.libs.F.Promise<play.mvc.Result> callback()
        This method handles the callback call from the provider to finish the authentication process. The credentials and then the profile of the authenticated user is retrieved and the originally requested url (or the specific saved url) is restored.
        Returns:
        the redirection to the saved request

      • logoutAndOk

        public static play.mvc.Result logoutAndOk()
        This method logouts the authenticated user and send him to a blank page.
        Returns:
        the redirection to the blank page

      • logoutAndRedirect

        public static play.mvc.Result logoutAndRedirect()
        This method logouts the authenticated user and send him to the url defined in the Constants.REDIRECT_URL_LOGOUT_PARAMETER_NAME parameter name or to the defaultLogoutUrl. This parameter is matched against the Config.getLogoutUrlPattern().
        Returns:
        the redirection to the "logout url"
